version_description: Https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GE7JvEsCGkc This is an acoustic version of the Taylor Swift Song Call it What You Want. First thing to remember is that we're in Drop D. It is likely that it could be played another way, but it's how you get the drone sound that runs throughout the song. Below are the chords in tab form. As they're in Drop D it's hard to pick exactly what chords they are so I've tabbed them out below. I used the chord finder on jamplay to work out the names of the chords so, feel free to correct if wrong. It's the same 4 chords played in the same order throughout.
This version is tabbed from a 24 second video of Taylor Swift playing the song in her house. The star indicates a single strum.
This tab is a basic chord version based off of her Saturday Night Live acoustic performance. Link to SNL performance video: https://youtu.be/GE7JvEsCGkc.

version_description: I tabbed this from her live performance on SNL. Please use the chord legend that I created and not the one auto generated by UG because it's way off.
From TS' new album Reputation. Stream/Watch: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V54CEElTF_U.
A take on an acoustic twist on this song. Pretty simplified version with no barre chords so it's good for beginners. Uses capo on 2nd fret.
This is just a really simple way to play the song. A great way for beginners to learn the song.
The third and final promotional single off of Taylor Swift's 2017 album "reputation". Enjoy :).
